theorem
Th28: (|. Ka .| c= ( [#] Ka ) implies ( BCS Ka ) is  affinely-independent)
proof
set P = ( BCS Ka );
set B = ( center_of_mass V );
assume |. Ka .| c= ( [#] Ka );
then A1: P = ( subdivision (B,Ka) ) by CKB26:def 1;
let A being (Subset of P);
assume A is  simplex-like;
then consider S being  c=-linear  finite  simplex-like (Subset-Family of Ka) such that A2: A = ( B .: S ) by A1,SIMPLEX0:def 20;
per cases ;
suppose S is  empty;

then A = ( {} ) by A2,RELAT_1:116;
hence thesis;
end;
suppose A3: S is non empty;

(S c= ( bool ( union S ) ) & ( bool ( @ ( union S ) ) ) c= ( bool (the carrier of V) )) by ZFMISC_1:67,ZFMISC_1:82;
then reconsider s = S as  c=-linear  finite (Subset-Family of V) by XBOOLE_1:1;
( union S ) in S by A3,SIMPLEX0:9;
then ( union S ) is  simplex-like by TOPS_2:def 1;
then ( @ ( union S ) ) is  affinely-independent;
then ( union s ) is  affinely-independent;
hence thesis by A2,RLAFFIN2:29;
end;
end;
